    type: string
    description: >-
      The concrete, independent consideration actually conferred on Employee in
      exchange for the covenants (for example, a signing bonus, a raise,
      specialized training, or another benefit beyond the mere offer or
      continuation of at-will employment).
    display_label: Independent Consideration
    default: >-
      a signing bonus, access to Employer's confidential information and
      customer relationships, and specialized training
    section: Timing
    default_value_rationale: >-
      Missouri consideration law is divided on whether continued at-will
      employment alone supports restrictive covenants. Reciting a concrete,
      independent benefit, rather than relying only on the offer or continuation
      of at-will employment, places the covenant on the safer side of that
      divide.
    rationale_source: case_law
    requirement_id: REQ-labor-and-employment-law.restrictive-covenant-agreement.missouri.support-covenant-with-independent-consideration
  - name: governing_law
    type: string
    description: Governing law state
    display_label: Governing Law
    section: Legal
    default: Missouri
  - name: confidentiality_trade_secret_duration
    type: string
    description: Duration of confidentiality obligations for trade secrets
    display_label: Trade Secrets Duration
    default: Perpetual
    section: Confidentiality
  - name: confidentiality_other_duration
    type: string
    description: Duration of confidentiality obligations for non-trade-secret information
    display_label: Other Confidential Information Duration
    default: 24 months
    section: Confidentiality
    default_value_rationale: >-
      24 months is common for non-trade-secret confidentiality obligations in
      employment agreements.
  - name: employee_nonsolicit_included
    type: boolean
    description: Whether the employee non-solicitation covenant is included
    display_label: Employee Non-Solicitation Included
    default: true
    section: Employee Non-Solicitation
  - name: employee_nonsolicit_duration
    type: string
    description: Duration of employee non-solicitation restriction
    display_label: Employee Non-Solicitation Duration
    default: 12 months
    section: Employee Non-Solicitation
    default_value_rationale: >-
      Missouri law gives employee no-hire and anti-raiding covenants a
      conclusive reasonableness presumption when the postemployment duration is
      no more than one year. Drawing this covenant to 12 months captures that
      statutory safe harbor; a longer term falls back to the
      facts-and-circumstances reasonableness test.
    rationale_source: legislation
    requirement_id: REQ-labor-and-employment-law.restrictive-covenant-agreement.missouri.keep-employee-no-hire-within-one-year-safe-harbor
  - name: covered_employee_period
    type: string
    description: >-
      Lookback period for determining which employees are covered by the
      non-solicitation restriction.
    display_label: Covered Employee Period
    default: 12 months
    section: Employee Non-Solicitation
    default_value_rationale: >-
      12 months is the most common lookback period for employee non-solicitation
      scope.
  - name: customer_nonsolicit_included
    type: boolean
    description: Whether the customer/partner non-solicitation covenant is included
    display_label: Customer Non-Solicitation Included
    default: true
    section: Customer Non-Solicitation
  - name: customer_nonsolicit_duration
    type: string
    description: Duration of customer/partner non-solicitation restriction
    display_label: Customer Non-Solicitation Duration
    default: 12 months
    section: Customer Non-Solicitation
    default_value_rationale: >-
      Missouri sets no statutory cap on a customer non-solicit, and the employee
      no-hire safe harbor does not reach customer restrictions, so the covenant
      is judged under the common-law reasonableness test. 12 months is a common,
      conservative duration counsel should size to the actual customer
      relationships protected; the covered class matters more than the number,
      because customer restrictions should be limited to customers the employee
      actually serviced or had substantial contact with.
    rationale_source: editorial
  - name: covered_customer_period
    type: string
    description: >-
      Lookback period for determining which customers are covered by the
      non-solicitation and non-dealing restrictions.
    display_label: Covered Customer Period
    default: 12 months
    section: Customer Non-Solicitation
    default_value_rationale: >-
      12 months is the most common lookback period for customer non-solicitation
      scope.
  - name: noncompete_included
    type: boolean
    description: >-
      Whether the non-competition covenant is included. Missouri has no general
      non-compete statute; a covenant not to compete begins as a presumptively
      void restraint on trade and is enforceable only to the extent it is
      demonstrably reasonable and protects the employer's trade secrets or
      customer contacts, with the employer bearing the burden on the protectable
      interest and on time/geographic reasonableness. This template recites the
      protectable-interest basis and sizes the restraint to the employer's actual
      footprint.
    display_label: Non-Competition Included
    default: false
    section: Non-Competition
    default_value_rationale: >-
      Conservative default. The non-compete is the most heavily scrutinized
      covenant under Missouri law, which enforces it only in service of trade
      secrets or customer contacts and never against mere competition; a customer
      non-solicit backstopped by the Missouri Uniform Trade Secrets Act often
      protects the employer as well. Include only after confirming an identified
      trade-secret or customer-contact interest and sizing the duration and
      territory to the actual footprint.
  - name: noncompete_duration
    type: string
    description: Duration of non-competition restriction
    display_label: Non-Competition Duration
    default: 12 months
    section: Non-Competition
    default_value_rationale: >-
      Missouri imposes no statutory cap on non-compete duration; restrictions of
      up to about two years are commonly within the range courts will consider,
      but that is a framing of case outcomes, not a safe-harbor number, and the
      employer must still justify the specific term on the facts. 12 months is a
      common, conservative default counsel should size to the actual role and
      market rather than copy from another form.
  - name: territory
    type: string
    description: Geographic scope of the non-competition restriction
    display_label: Restricted Territory
    default: the geographic area in which Employee provided services
    section: Non-Competition
    default_value_rationale: >-
      Tied to the employee's actual service area. Missouri case law puts the
      employer to its proof on geographic reasonableness, and a covenant with no
      territorial limit risks both nonenforcement and no judicial rewrite. A
      narrower area genuinely needed to protect the trade-secret or
      customer-contact interest is far easier to defend.
    rationale_source: case_law
    requirement_id: REQ-labor-and-employment-law.restrictive-covenant-agreement.missouri.limit-covenants-to-trade-secrets-or-customer-contacts
  - name: competitive_business_definition
    type: string
    description: >-
      Description of the business activities that constitute competition with
      the employer.
    display_label: Competitive Business
    section: Non-Competition
  - name: specified_competitors
    type: string
    description: >-
      Optional named list of specific competitors. Narrowing the restriction to
      named competitors strengthens enforceability.
    display_label: Specified Competitors
    default: ''
    section: Non-Competition
  - name: nondealing_included
    type: boolean
    description: Whether the no-business-with-covered-customers covenant is included.
    display_label: No Business with Covered Customers Included
    default: false
    section: No Business with Covered Customers
  - name: nondealing_duration
    type: string
    description: Duration of the no-business-with-covered-customers restriction
    display_label: No Business with Covered Customers Duration
    default: 12 months
    section: No Business with Covered Customers
  - name: passive_public_holdings_threshold
    type: string
    description: >-
      Maximum ownership percentage of publicly traded securities permitted under
      the Passive Public Holdings carveout.
    display_label: Passive Public Holdings Threshold
    default: five percent
    section: Definitions
    default_value_rationale: >-
      Five percent of any class of publicly traded securities is the standard
      passive investment carveout across restrictive covenant agreements.
  - name: noninvestment_included
    type: boolean
    description: Whether the non-investment covenant is included.
    display_label: Non-Investment Included
    default: false
    section: Non-Investment
  - name: noninvestment_duration
    type: string
    description: Duration of non-investment restriction
    display_label: Non-Investment Duration
    default: 12 months
    section: Non-Investment
  - name: nondisparagement_duration
    type: string
    description: Duration of non-disparagement obligation (measured from termination)
    display_label: Non-Disparagement Duration
    default: 24 months
    section: Non-Disparagement
    default_value_rationale: 24 months is common for employment non-disparagement provisions.
priority_fields:
  - employer_name
